	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Channels are numbered differently in United States and Japanese video broadcast systems due to different radio communication regulations.
<br />
<br /><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Television_channel_frequencies" class="postlink">Wikipedia:Television channel frequencies</a> says Japan puts channel 1 on 91.25 MHz and channel 2 on 97.25 MHz. These fall in the rawther gap between channels 6 and 7 in American TV. <a href="http://www.jneuhaus.com/fccindex/cablech.html" class="postlink">Jneuhaus:Cable TV Channel Frequencies</a> claims that US standard cable channel 95 is indeed the same frequency as Japanese channel 1.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
